SUMMARY:Waiting for Naseer
DESCRIPTION:Language: Hindi and English \nTwo actors are waiting at the Prithvi Theatre café for a chance to watch their favourite actor\, Naseeruddin Shah\, perform. But there is a catch: only one of them has a ticket\, and both of them are already dead. Their desperate longing for that one elusive ticket becomes a meditation on ambition\, jealousy\, friendship\, artistic obsession\, and the strange ways in which performers measure their lives. \nWritten by Sapan Saran and directed by Srinivas Beesetty\, Waiting for Naseer is a celebration of theatre\, passion and the artist within all of us. Filled with humour\, tenderness and absurdity\, the play reminds us that perhaps the struggle itself is enough to fill a person’s heart. \nIn collaboration with: \n\n          \nSupported by: \n \n\n\nA Philosophical Comedy about Waiting\nFor Ages 14+\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc7kmgOJcP2kP0NfND3WjRSS70RUPghzQf6z1DWlpmJET-4MA/viewform?usp=publish-editor)\n*Cast & Crew*: Maulik Pandey\, Maahir Mohiuddin\, Naman Roy\, Chaitali Das\n*Event Categories*: Performing Arts\, Theatre
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/waiting-for-naseer/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Performing Arts,Theatre
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Thumbnail-4.jpg
