UID:91395-1783794600-1783800000@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:From Stage to Screen to Page
DESCRIPTION:A ghost is loose in Tagore’s fiction. \nHer name is Kadambari Devi. She was Tagore’s sister-in-law in real life\, and now she has time-travelled to talk with two of his heroines about the choices they made. As the three women debate\, challenge\, and inspire one another\, they discover a surprising truth: the world may have moved from the 19th century to the 21st\, but the inner battles women fight for independence\, desire\, and meaning\, remain strikingly familiar. \nThree Women — A Graphic Novel is adapted from Isheeta Ganguly’s musical\, Three Women: A Musical Theatre. This evening\, she joins Vani Kola in conversation\, with dramatised readings from the book by Isheeta and Swati De and an audience Q&A to close \nIn collaboration with: \n \n\n\nAn Illustrative Reimagining of Tagore’s Iconic Heroines\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScZA5eEVZhTO053ehau74VDcScxY8gsiIUsCEXwmqkYheVN8Q/viewform?usp=pp_url)\n*Speakers*: Isheeta Ganguly\, Vani Kola\, Swati De\n*Event Categories*: Books\, Gender\, Visual Arts
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/from-stage-to-screen-to-page/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Gender,Visual Arts
