SUMMARY:Designing Belonging\, Expanding Justice
DESCRIPTION:Adnan Zillur Morshed\, author of Spatial (In)Justice: How Does It Manifest in the Built Environment? is in conversation with architect Prem Chandavarkar and social anthropologist Carol Upadhya.  \nTogether they examine how justice and space intersect\, producing different meanings for different constituencies. From Aristotle and Kant to John Rawls and Amartya Sen\, from Rural Studio to Planet of Slums\, from Black Lives Matter to sustainability initiatives: they ask what three decades of theoretical debates and design activism have actually produced. \nIf spatial justice is achieved in the built environment\, what might such a space look and feel like? And who gets to decide? \n\n\nWhose Space? Whose City?\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdotabWeayBz9lU-FzL0eJyAHNvwHsHSRo6pIIPfXUCybgdNw/viewform?usp=publish-editor)\n*Speakers*: Adnan Zillur Morshed\, Prem Chandavarkar\, Carol Upadhya\n*Event Categories*: Books\, Cities
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/designing-belonging-expanding-justice/
